Purpose
This file is the command-line entry point for the demo program.

Linear intent
1. Open the Cmdliner API so the demo can expose a real CLI instead of ad hoc argument parsing.
2. Define the `--config` option so the user can choose which JSON runtime configuration file to load.
3. Define the `--task-id` option so the user can override the task id without editing the config file.
4. Define the positional `INPUT` argument so the user can override the demo prompt from the command line.
5. In `run`, load the runtime configuration and fail early with a clean CLI error if the file cannot be parsed.
6. Resolve the final task id by preferring the CLI override and falling back to the configuration value.
7. Resolve the final input text by preferring the CLI override and falling back to the configuration value.
8. Execute the framework through `Agent_graph.run` inside `Lwt_main.run`.
9. Print the task id so the run is easy to identify.
10. Print the completed agent names so the user can see which path the orchestration followed.
11. Print the final payload in a human-readable form.
12. Register the command metadata and exit through `Cmd.eval`.

